1928 New York Giants Results

The New York Giants of the National Football League ended the 1928 season with a record of 4 wins and 7 losses and 2 ties, finishing sixth in the NFL.

New York ran up 79 points, while the leaky defense yielded 136.

Earl Potteiger coached the team.
